criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient with Parkinson's disease selected for deep brain stimulation (DBS) of the
             subthalamic nucleus (STN) in accordance with the criteria established by Welter and
             colleagues (Welter et al., 2002);

          -  Aged 18 years or above;

          -  Written informed consent from the patient.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient under a legal incapacity or with limited legal capacity;

          -  Patient who has perioperative complications or postoperative confusion;

          -  Patient displaying cognitive disturbances involving the early stages of speech
             processing (on the basis of an audiogram systematically conducted prior to surgery) ;

          -  Patient displaying cognitive disturbances involving the early stages of face
             processing (on the basis of the Benton Facial Recognition Test (Benton, Hamsher,
             Varney, & Spreen, 1983) systematically administered prior to surgery);

          -  Patient incapable of understanding the information given about the study, performing
             the tasks or providing informed consent.
